To compile all plugins you need:

- gcc-c   C compiler
- gcc-c++ (for aspell support)
- automake 1.7 or better
- libtool 1.4e or better

- glib 2.2.0 - http://www.gtk.org
- gtk+ 2.4.0 - http://www.gtk.org - GUI
- libtlen - http://libtlen.sourceforge.net - Tlen
- Loudmouth 0.17 or newer http://www.imendio.com/projects/loudmouth - Jabber
- xosd - http://ignavus.net/software.html - XOSD
- esound - http://www.tux.org/~ricdude/EsounD.html - sound-esd
- audiofile - http://www.68k.org/~michael/audiofile
- aRts! - http://www.arts-project.org - sound-arts
- gtkspell - http://gtkspell.sourceforge.net
- gnutls - http://www.gnu.org/software/gnutls - gadu-gadu
- dbus - http://www.freedesktop.org/software/dbus

WARNING: very experimental perl support will compile/work only on Linux!

Read doc/problems and other documentation files BEFORE submitting ANY
bugreports to http://bugs.gnugadu.org

Important:

    If you accidentally do something wrong with list of plugins to be loaded,
    try removing $HOME/.gg2/modules.load and restart GNU Gadu so it will load 
    all available plugins.

Skins:
    
    Skins should be installed in $HOME/.gg2/skins/<skindir> directory or 
$HOME/$HOME_ETC/gg2/skins/<skindir> (if You have $HOME_ETC set).
    
    GNU Gadu uses skin in Windows Gadu-Gadu client format.

